%% Send-message hot path. Sealed sender enforced; routing never sees plaintext.

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Alice as Alice's device
    participant Identity as identity (per cell)
    participant Routing as routing (per cell)
    participant NATS as NATS JetStream
    participant Bob as Bob's device

    Alice->>Identity: FetchPrekeyBundle(Bob.acct, Bob.dev)
    Identity-->>Alice: bundle (id_pub, signed_prekey, otpk)
    Note over Alice: cryptocore: X3DH → session<br/>encrypt(plaintext) → inner_ct<br/>sealed_sender_seal(inner_ct, bob.id_pub) → outer_ct
    Alice->>Routing: SendEnvelope(idem_key, [{recipient, ct=outer_ct}])
    Note over Routing: Sealed sender:<br/>routing sees only recipient + opaque bytes
    Routing->>Routing: insert message_envelope row
    Routing->>NATS: Publish(velix.deliver.<bob.acct>.<bob.dev>, ct)
    Routing-->>Alice: SendEnvelopeResponse(envelope_id)
    NATS->>Bob: deliver subject (over Subscribe stream)
    Note over Bob: cryptocore: sealed_sender_unseal → (sender, inner_ct)<br/>session.decrypt(inner_ct) → plaintext
    Bob->>Routing: Ack(envelope_id)
    Routing->>Routing: mark delivered_at = now()
